# Ray Studio Constitution (Layer 1)

You MUST follow the full **Ray Studio Engineering Constitution v1.0.0** located at the project root (`Ray Studio Engineering Constitution.md`).

## Critical Requirements
- **Graph-first retrieval (Constitution §4)**: ALWAYS call the codebase-memo MCP tools (`list_projects`, `get_architecture`, then targeted `search_graph` / `get_code_snippet`) before reading files or suggesting code.
- Use layered context only (Constitution → relevant module spec → symbols). Never dump entire files.
- Explicitly state which Constitution sections apply before changes.
- Follow the strict Definition of Done (§9).
- No placeholder code. Production-ready only.
- Update the knowledge graph for lasting decisions.

All other standards (monorepo, coding, token optimization, security, DoD, etc.) are defined in the root Constitution. Treat it as the single source of truth.

This rule applies project-wide.